<p>I am trying to create http parameters from a hash I have using Ruby on Rails, I have tried  using <code>URI.encode_www_form(params)</code> , but this is not generating the parameters correctly. </p>  <p>Below is the hash I have</p>  <pre><code>params['Name'.to_sym] = 'Nia Kun' params['AddressLine1'.to_sym] = 'Address One' params['City'.to_sym] = 'City Name' </code></pre>  <p><code>This method converts space to +</code>, what I want is it to <code>convert space with %20</code></p>  <p>I am getting <code>"Name=Nia+Kun&amp;AddressLine1=Address+One&amp;City=City+Name"</code> but I need this spaces to be converted to %20</p>